1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:50,140
[Previously]
It’s none of the girl’s business. Just keep your mouth shut.

25
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,380
When it comes to using brains,

26
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,780
better let the guys handle that.

27
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,900
[Pheempat]: You want to do something to help the Wachara Group, right?

28
00:01:56,539 --> 00:01:59,100
I’ll try to get close to Miss Apo as soon as I can.

29
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:01,580
You’ll definitely beat the Watin Group this time.

30
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:04,780
[Nam]: Pretty faces with no brains are not welcome here.

31
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:07,420
[Lada]: We all make mistakes, don’t we?

32
00:02:07,420 --> 00:02:09,300
If you fire me,

33
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,580
you might make a big mistake there.

34
00:02:11,580 --> 00:02:12,900
All of you together?

35
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,940
[Preem]: But if you want me to find an excuse to fire her…

36
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:15,740
[Nam]: No need.

37
00:02:16,460 --> 00:02:18,500
Just keep reporting me as it is.

38
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,540
[Lom]: Has Miss Lada been working here long?

39
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:21,820
Why would you want to know about her?

40
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:23,100
I want to ask her out.

41
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:24,020
This one is off limit.

42
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:25,460
[Lom]: Hold on.

43
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:53,160
So many guests today.

44
00:02:54,730 --> 00:02:57,140
I can’t believe we’re entering a low season now.

45
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:59,000
How are you getting along, Lada?

46
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,180
You’re working two shifts in a row. Are you sure you can manage?

47
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:10,180
See? That’s why I told you to do the night shift another day.

48
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:15,340
Boss

49
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,740
Yes, Boss.

50
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,380
Chonlada.

51
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,260
Miss Chonlada!

52
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:40,180
Good evening! Welcome to Monarch Global International!

53
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,420
Were you on an auto-reply mode or what?

54
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,100
Boss?

55
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,400
You’re a receptionist.

56
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:07,340
Do you think it’s appropriate to take a nap while you’re on duty?

57
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,330
I was just…

58
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:14,940
Don’t tell me you had no idea you were napping?

59
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,530
You, take it from here.

60
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,200
Yes, Boss.

61
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,060
And you…

62
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:33,180
Come with me.

63
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:45,380
She’ll definitely fire me.

64
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:00,980
[Lom: Sis, are you hiding Chonlada from me?]

65
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,780
Boss.

66
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:05,420
Boss, I’m so sorry. I didn’t mean it.

67
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:07,500
I promise I won’t mess up again.

68
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,420
Please don’t fire me.

69
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:10,940
Please, Boss.
[Lom: Not picking up. Read but no reply. Do you think you can stop me?]

70
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,300
Go over there and sit.

71
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,020
Yes?

72
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:17,500
Go sit over there.

73
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,900
Why do you want me to sit there?

74
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,500
Just do as I said.

75
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:28,200
[Lom: You’re in the office, right?]
But what you said doesn’t make sense.

76
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:32,020
You might be the boss, but you should also have a good reason to make your staff do as you say.

77
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:36,200
So, why do you want me to stay here with you?

78
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:41,540
[Lom: Stay right there!]

79
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:49,860
[Lom: Don’t go anywhere!]

80
00:06:00,140 --> 00:06:03,180
[Nam: Go back to your room. Just do as you’re told.]

81
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,260
You like her, don’t you?

82
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:31,960
I already told you.

83
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:34,420
If you don’t, why are you hiding her from me?

84
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,820
You want to keep her away from me, don’t you?

85
00:06:37,159 --> 00:06:38,560
You’ve been drinking, haven’t you?

86
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,330
Just go back to your room.

87
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,530
And listen, I’ll tell you something.

88
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:45,580
If you don’t want your life to get complicated
you’d better stay away from her.

89
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:46,760
Boss.

90
00:06:48,730 --> 00:06:49,900
Isn’t that Chonlada?

91
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,060
Where are you now?

92
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:56,780
I…I’ve got work to do.

93
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:57,540
Talk to you later.

94
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:03,660
Hey! Can’t you see I was on the phone?

95
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:07,660
I do. It’s you who couldn’t see me.

96
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:09,500
That’s why I have to stick out my face like this.

97
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:13,300
I still don’t understand why you want me to stay with you in this meeting room?

98
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,940
If there’s nothing else, please excuse me. I have to go downstairs.

99
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:24,100
Nuch just told me Miss Wayo is looking for me.

100
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:26,860
Where are you going?

101
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,620
I told you Nuch said Miss Wayo is looking for me.

102
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,200
Then why do you have to go?

103
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,300
To take care of her room, of course.

104
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:42,260
I already told Miss Wadee to take care of it.

105
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:43,460
Stay here.

106
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:48,360
I told her that too. But Nuch insists that Miss Wayo really wants to see me.

107
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,400
She is a guest at our hotel too.

108
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,460
Not to mention that she’s also your sister.

109
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:56,400
I don't want to get complaint that I was being negligent.

110
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:58,330
Please excuse me, Boss.

111
00:08:02,260 --> 00:08:03,180
Sit here.

112
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:07,820
Sit and stay as quiet as you can.

113
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,740
I’ll be right back. I have a job for you.

114
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,580
- But, Boss!
- Quiet!

115
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:17,330
If you disobey me again,

116
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,580
I’ll fire you this time.

117
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:22,860
And you can go on and threaten me
or file a charge against me for an unfair dismissal.

118
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,220
I don’t give a damn at all!

119
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:35,260
So mean!

120
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,620
Possessive of your sister, aren’t you? Good!

121
00:08:44,330 --> 00:08:48,020
You’d better keep me close for a long long time, Boss.

122
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:30,020
Hey.

123
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:04,420
She’s so weird. How can she sleep anywhere like this?

124
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,700
3am?

125
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:57,140
If you’re up, just leave. No need to wake me.

126
00:11:57,140 --> 00:12:01,580
And tell the maid to do the ozone,

127
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:04,860
cleaning for the couch to prevent the mold from growing on it. You’re drooling in your sleep.

128
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:10,820
I’m not that dirty.

129
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,560
Are you saying I’m dirty?

130
00:12:51,930 --> 00:12:52,780
Just you wait.

131
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:32,140
Someone is in there?

132
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,900
This is going to be juicy.

133
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:51,940
[Maid group]: Got a big fat juicy gossip.

134
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:19,740
Lada.

135
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:20,930
Nuch.

136
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:22,780
You’re here so early.

137
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:24,860
I’ve been waiting for you.

138
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:25,960
Why?

139
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,380
What happened?

140
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:29,800
Don’t tell me…

141
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,900
that Boss wants me to do something for her again.

142
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:34,860
That’s right, it’s about our boss.

143
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:36,500
But it’s not about work.

144
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:43,780
Then what is it about?

145
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:46,100
So, did you sleep with her?

146
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:55,380
I’m sorry. Is that what people are talking about?

147
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:59,980
Doesn’t anyone think that Boss and I were only discussing about work in that room?

148
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:05,460
You and Boss came out of that room after three in the morning.

149
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:07,820
I’ve tried my best to believe it was only about work.

150
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:11,900
But all these years that I’ve been working for the Watin Group,

151
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:17,660
I’ve never seen Boss summon anyone to discuss about work so late at night apart from Miss Preem and you.

152
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,060
Not even one?

153
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,180
No.

154
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:30,380
And unlike you, none of the staff who dares to talk back to her has ever managed to keep their job here after that.

155
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:35,980
She also talks to you more often than she’s ever talked to any of us here.

156
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,900
Well, that’s…

157
00:15:40,180 --> 00:15:42,860
Nuch, please listen.

158
00:15:42,860 --> 00:15:45,140
Actually…
- Right now, every staff here…

159
00:15:45,140 --> 00:15:49,260
thinks that you and Boss already slept together.

160
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:54,140
So, don’t bother trying to explain anything.

161
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,180
Nobody would listen to you.

162
00:15:56,730 --> 00:15:59,940
Read my lips…”Impossible”.

163
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:12,140
But I wasn’t trying to deny it.

164
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,940
What do you mean?

165
00:16:18,930 --> 00:16:22,460
So, you and Boss really…

166
00:16:23,460 --> 00:16:24,260
did it?

167
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,460
Geez, Nuch.

168
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:30,540
I’m a lady somehow.

169
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:33,900
Don’t make me say it out loud.

170
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:39,540
Let’s just say, I’ll leave it to Boss to clarify it herself.

171
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,580
So…

172
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,580
How many times?

173
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:06,619
Actually, I’m not that hungry.

174
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:08,060
I’d better get back to work.

175
00:17:09,099 --> 00:17:10,579
- Let’go then.
- Okay.

176
00:17:18,730 --> 00:17:21,940
[Nam]: Miss Preem, is there a problem among our staff lately?

177
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:26,300
Since I’ve walked in, I could feel them looking my way and whispering to each other.

178
00:17:26,530 --> 00:17:28,500
As if they were gossiping about me.

179
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:31,340
[Preem]: That’s probably because of the rumour lately.

180
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:33,780
But I honestly have no idea who started it.

181
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:35,500
[Nam]: What rumour?

182
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,330
Watch out, Boss!

183
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,200
Boss.

184
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:48,900
Are you okay, Boss?

185
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:52,820
I’m okay.

186
00:18:01,660 --> 00:18:03,100
[Lom’s calling]

187
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:12,130
Is she calling about the rumour?

188
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:18,020
I thought you said Lom already checked out.

189
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:20,380
Why do you think she’d know about the rumour?

190
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,340
She’s a cop somehow.

191
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:26,740
And she knows most of the staff here.

192
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,860
It’s possible that she’d hear about it.

193
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:32,730
Do you want me to stop this rumour?

194
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:36,500
Never mind.

195
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:40,300
You know I don’t like to waste my time on something nonsense like this.

196
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,980
And since it’s just a rumour, we’d better let it go.

197
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,460
They’ll forget it soon.

198
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:48,160
But people don’t usually forget this kind of thing, Boss.

199
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:57,900
Well…if anyone wants to waste their time believing that, just let them be.

200
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,820
I couldn’t care less.

201
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,740
Thank you.

202
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:24,220
Hey, it’s already lunch time. Why are you two still working, busy bees?

203
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:25,940
Hello, Big Boss.

204
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:28,860
Big Boss! Hello.

205
00:19:28,860 --> 00:19:32,620
Long time no see indeed. I wonder what brought you here today.

206
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,060
Probably to see the lady boss, am I right?

207
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:40,260
She’s in the office. Let me take you there then.

208
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:41,540
-This way, please.
- Oh, but…

209
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,060
I’m afraid she already left.

210
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:46,330
But the last time I checked, she's still in the office.

211
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,560
She has gone out.

212
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:50,500
Hold on! Stop it.

213
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,300
You two haven’t changed one bit.

214
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:55,540
One minute, you’re friends. Then you’re at each other’s throat.

215
00:19:56,960 --> 00:20:00,800
Well, today…I’m not here to see Nam.

216
00:20:05,530 --> 00:20:06,780
I’m here to see…

217
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,500
Are you Chonlada?

218
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:19,980
Er…Yes, I’m Chonlada.

219
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:24,580
I’m here to see you, Chonlada.

220
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,580
- What?
- What?

221
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,340
It’s already lunch time, isn’t it?

222
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:34,200
How come Nam still keeps you hustling with work.

223
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,940
She’s such a bad boss.

224
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:44,900
Come and have lunch with me, will you?

225
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:47,820
I have a lot to talk to you.

226
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:13,100
Where is Chonlada?

227
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,460
Big Boss, can you eat spicy food?

228
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:23,620
It seems I ended up ordering only spicy dishes.

229
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:25,580
Sure.

230
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,140
Come on, let’s dig in.

231
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:30,980
By the way, you know what?

232
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:33,620
Since we’re not working right now,

233
00:21:34,180 --> 00:21:36,180
you can stop calling me Big Boss.

234
00:21:36,940 --> 00:21:39,020
Call me ‘Dad’ like Nam does.

235
00:21:41,930 --> 00:21:44,340
Oh, that’s all right.

236
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:49,940
I think it’d be more appropriate to call you Big Boss like the others.

237
00:21:51,730 --> 00:21:53,540
But you’re Nam’s girlfriend, aren’t you?

238
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:57,500
I heard you’re seeing each other.

239
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,100
No, that’s not it.

240
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:03,780
My relationship with Miss Apo is strictly professional—just a boss and an employee.

241
00:22:06,730 --> 00:22:09,780
No need to be afraid. You can be honest with me.

242
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:13,900
I might be old but I’m quite open when it comes to love.

243
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:20,260
Whether with a girl or a guy, as long as you love each other;

244
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,660
I’m happy for you both.

245
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:31,700
So…Nam is a workaholic, isn’t she?

246
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:35,100
All she does is work and barely has time for you.

247
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:40,020
Don’t worry, I’ll talk to her about it.

248
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:43,340
It’s not like that.

249
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:48,500
I don’t think being workaholic is a bad thing.

250
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:52,740
On the other hand, I see it more like a dedication in work.

251
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:55,140
And I actually find it very charming.

252
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,420
Huh? Do you really think that?

253
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:02,140
Yes, I also love to work.

254
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:04,860
If the person I am seeing also loves to work like me,

255
00:23:04,860 --> 00:23:07,260
I’ll support her fully.

256
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:13,060
I can’t believe it. There’s still someone who understands her.

257
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:23,260
Listen, thank you so much for coming into my daughter’s life.

258
00:23:32,730 --> 00:23:35,740
Dad, why are you taking my staff out here?

259
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:38,460
Why, of course, to have lunch.

260
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:46,500
I just want to get to know the person you’re dating.

261
00:23:51,260 --> 00:23:52,760
Chonlada and I are not dating.

262
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:58,860
No need to hide it from me.

263
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,580
I already approved of you and her seeing each other.

264
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:05,340
That’s because…

265
00:24:06,820 --> 00:24:08,300
I like you, Lada.

266
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:17,620
Chonlada. Chonlada!

267
00:24:19,130 --> 00:24:22,060
Get up. Or do you want to stay here?

268
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:28,940
Please excuse me.

269
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:34,460
Boss!

270
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:35,700
Please listen to me first, Boss.

271
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,580
I didn’t ask him to take me out for lunch.

272
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:38,260
Boss!

273
00:24:38,260 --> 00:24:39,700
Your dad invited me out!

274
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:40,960
How could I say no to him?

275
00:24:41,130 --> 00:24:42,540
Hey, Boss! Did you hear what…

276
00:25:14,730 --> 00:25:16,460
You’re such a troublemaker.

277
00:25:17,260 --> 00:25:18,900
It’s true that my dad invited you.

278
00:25:19,130 --> 00:25:20,860
But there’s a way to turn down his offer.

279
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,940
You’re making everyone here getting the wrong idea.

280
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:28,860
You’re blaming me? Don’t you accuse me like that!

281
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,140
Isn’t this all your fault?

282
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:31,980
What did I do?

283
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,360
If you hadn’t locked me up in that room until morning,

284
00:25:35,730 --> 00:25:37,380
no one would have seen us at all.

285
00:25:38,530 --> 00:25:39,980
Then, go and fix the rumour.

286
00:25:40,660 --> 00:25:42,780
Tell everyone what actually happened.

287
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:46,100
You’re the boss.

288
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:49,860
Go tell them yourself. They will definitely listen to you.

289
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:55,540
But if they don’t hear it from your side too, how can we settle it?

290
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,130
We have to tell them the same side of the story.

291
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:01,460
Then let them think all they want.

292
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,800
Because after all, it’s not true anyway.

293
00:26:04,530 --> 00:26:06,460
It’s not like I like you, Chonlada.

294
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:17,420
You’re such a control freak!

295
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:20,260
What was that?

296
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,100
At first, I was planning to find a way to get us out of this.

297
00:26:24,660 --> 00:26:27,060
But after seeing how you react, I’ve changed my mind.

298
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,460
I couldn’t be bothered.

299
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,420
What a waste of time.

300
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:35,620
Chonlada.

301
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:47,100
Yes, Miss Preem?

302
00:26:47,660 --> 00:26:49,460
Miss Lom wants to see you, Boss.

303
00:26:51,330 --> 00:26:52,220
Where is she now?

304
00:26:59,730 --> 00:27:01,060
Ouch, that hurts!

305
00:27:03,780 --> 00:27:05,100
- Let me go!
- Don’t!

306
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:08,340
If you get out of the car, I’ll fire you.

307
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:47,300
Why are you taking me here?

308
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,340
Obviously not to kill you and dump your body here.

309
00:27:50,820 --> 00:27:53,940
I’ve wasted enough time with all this nonsense.

310
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,530
Then take me back.

311
00:27:58,100 --> 00:27:59,780
Do you think I drove here…

312
00:28:00,060 --> 00:28:01,540
only to let you boss me around?

313
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:03,300
I’ll go back myself then.

314
00:28:05,930 --> 00:28:07,620
You can’t go now.

315
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:17,820
You often say something and mean another, don't you?

316
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:20,900
Why?

317
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:24,260
You said you don’t like me, that you don’t want to stay close to me.

318
00:28:24,260 --> 00:28:27,700
But all you do is trying to keep me with you alone.

319
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:30,700
I wonder if you want to stop the rumour or escalate it even more.

320
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,620
That’s not what I think.

321
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:42,220
Then, why are you taking me here?

322
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:46,300
To stop the rumour about us.

323
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:50,160
Then, try talking to me nicely.

324
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:54,300
You’re crossing the line, Chonlada.

325
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,340
Is that a no?

326
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:04,580
Since you have no problem with me,

327
00:29:04,860 --> 00:29:07,260
how about we make the rumour come true then?

328
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:16,660
If you refuse to talk to me nicely,

329
00:29:16,930 --> 00:29:19,340
then have fun living with the rumour.

330
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,130
Chonlada!

331
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:39,760
Miss Chonlada!

332
00:29:44,100 --> 00:29:45,560
Can we talk, please?

333
00:29:50,100 --> 00:29:53,540
Oh, so you've agreed to talk to me nicely, Boss?

334
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:58,460
Please tell me your plan.

335
00:30:00,060 --> 00:30:00,980
Oh dear.

336
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:02,930
I’m afraid it’s too late, Boss

337
00:30:03,130 --> 00:30:04,700
I already called the cab.

338
00:30:04,930 --> 00:30:06,160
It should arrive in a minute.

339
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:07,980
Please excuse me then.

340
00:30:09,540 --> 00:30:10,700
Wait!

341
00:30:11,730 --> 00:30:12,730
You can’t leave.

342
00:30:17,660 --> 00:30:18,660
Why?

343
00:30:19,180 --> 00:30:23,380
Or are you afraid I’ll go back to see Miss Wayo at the hotel?

344
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:27,500
How did you know she’s at the hotel?

345
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,380
Miss Wayo has come looking for me especially.

346
00:30:32,020 --> 00:30:35,620
Don’t you think the staff would be talking?

347
00:30:36,930 --> 00:30:37,730
You’re really…

348
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:41,420
I never thought you’d be possessive of your sister.

349
00:30:41,420 --> 00:30:43,940
Wait, or are you actually…

350
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:48,980
possessive of me?

351
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:51,180
You can believe whatever you want.

352
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:53,930
But if you don’t tell me your plan,

353
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:56,300
I’ll take care of it my way.

354
00:30:57,130 --> 00:30:57,940
How?

355
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:02,580
Whatever the cause of the problem is,

356
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:05,220
I’ll just get rid of it.

357
00:31:06,730 --> 00:31:10,180
Are you going to fire me, Boss?

358
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,140
That’s fine!

359
00:31:18,460 --> 00:31:21,020
Weren’t you begging for a second chance back then?

360
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:22,700
I thought you didn’t want to get fired.

361
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:25,780
But right now I have backups like Big Boss and Miss Wayo.

362
00:31:25,780 --> 00:31:28,260
I’m pretty sure if your dad knows,

363
00:31:28,260 --> 00:31:29,500
he wouldn’t allow you to fire me.

364
00:31:29,700 --> 00:31:30,940
Tell me your plan!

365
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:33,380
-But…
- Quickly!

366
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:36,660
So, you’re not going to fire me now?

367
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:38,620
Just tell me.

368
00:31:40,860 --> 00:31:44,500
If you want me to tell you, try asking me nicely first.

369
00:31:47,930 --> 00:31:49,300
Smile a little.

370
00:31:54,360 --> 00:32:01,060
All right. The only way to stop this rumour is to make it about work.

371
00:32:10,660 --> 00:32:11,780
Impossible.

372
00:32:13,130 --> 00:32:14,860
Why impossible?

373
00:32:16,500 --> 00:32:19,820
You want me to suddenly promote you to be Miss Preem’s assistant.

374
00:32:20,130 --> 00:32:21,460
What would other people think?

375
00:32:23,300 --> 00:32:26,180
Well, they’d think it was all about work that kept us together,

376
00:32:26,180 --> 00:32:27,980
until three in the morning that night.

377
00:32:28,660 --> 00:32:30,180
Like they would believe it.

378
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,340
Probably not at first.

379
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:37,660
But after I get promoted, they’ll surely believe it.

380
00:32:38,660 --> 00:32:40,580
But we’ve never had that position before.

381
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:55,460
[Meeting Room 2]

382
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,140
Where are you going, Boss?

383
00:33:04,460 --> 00:33:05,940
To inspect work by the beach.

384
00:33:07,530 --> 00:33:09,460
But you have a meeting in 10 minutes.

385
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:18,420
I have a meeting today?

386
00:33:19,260 --> 00:33:23,100
Yes, you’ve called for a meeting with the marketing and PR teams…

387
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,180
to discuss about our hotel’s new campaign.

388
00:33:25,780 --> 00:33:28,980
Do you want me to postpone it?

389
00:33:29,660 --> 00:33:30,900
No, leave it be.

390
00:33:32,730 --> 00:33:34,220
Are you all right, Boss?

391
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:38,220
I can postpone the meeting if you want to get some rest.

392
00:33:39,700 --> 00:33:40,500
I’m fine.

393
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:43,220
But you’ve never forgotten your schedule before.

394
00:33:48,260 --> 00:33:50,180
If there’s anything I can help, you can always say it.

395
00:33:56,060 --> 00:33:57,060
Miss Preem.

396
00:33:58,140 --> 00:34:00,180
Do you want an assistant?

397
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:09,060
Sure, Ma’am. Just a moment, please.

398
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:12,100
Please fill in the information here, sir.

399
00:34:12,860 --> 00:34:13,659
Thank you.

400
00:34:15,260 --> 00:34:17,260
- Nuch.
- Yes?

401
00:34:17,260 --> 00:34:19,540
I can take it from here if you want.

402
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:21,940
Oh, that’s all right, Lada.

403
00:34:21,940 --> 00:34:24,420
Didn’t you just have lunch?

404
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:27,500
Why don’t you go sit and relax for a while first?

405
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:29,600
I can do it.

406
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,330
It’s really nothing, Lada.

407
00:34:36,330 --> 00:34:38,540
But if you do want to help, then…Here.

408
00:34:39,730 --> 00:34:44,260
Can you please handle the guests who might want to check in online? That’s all.

409
00:34:44,460 --> 00:34:46,060
I’ll take care of the rest.

410
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:47,260
Sure.

411
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:57,760
How nice.

412
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:00,900
Messing around to create a rumour…

413
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:03,820
so that you don’t have to work.

414
00:35:05,530 --> 00:35:07,100
Miss Chonlada.

415
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:15,620
You can go with Miss Preem.

416
00:35:15,620 --> 00:35:19,380
She just told me you’re no longer working for this department.

417
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:21,060
You’ll be transferred to another unit.

418
00:35:21,060 --> 00:35:22,860
Excuse me? Transferred?

419
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:27,500
Where…where will she be transferred to?

420
00:35:29,130 --> 00:35:30,060
Please come with me.

421
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:33,460
I’ve already set up a desk for you as my assistant.

422
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:36,380
Assistant?

423
00:35:53,700 --> 00:35:55,260
So, Miss Wadee.

424
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:59,260
Is Lada now Miss Preem’s assistant?

425
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:02,740
That’s right. Miss Preem said

426
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:06,260
Chonalada is quite productive, plus she can speak many languages.

427
00:36:06,260 --> 00:36:08,860
She also has good management skills.

428
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:11,340
She has been helping Miss Preem lately.

429
00:36:12,260 --> 00:36:15,400
That night when she was seen leaving the meeting room with Boss,

430
00:36:15,660 --> 00:36:17,980
it was because she had to do the work for Miss Preem.

431
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:20,300
No doubt the rumour isn’t true at all.

432
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,540
Now, has that answered your question?

433
00:36:24,540 --> 00:36:26,260
Yes, crystal clear.

434
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:35,420
Miss Preem.

435
00:36:36,420 --> 00:36:41,620
When you said you’ve prepared a desk for me, is it around here?

436
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:48,340
Of course not. It’s upstairs next to my desk, in front of Boss’s office.

437
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:52,580
Then…why are you taking me here?

438
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:57,600
Today, you have to go with Boss to meet with her appointments.

439
00:36:58,860 --> 00:37:01,400
What about you? Aren’t you coming with us?

440
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:13,380
You might be her assistant,

441
00:37:13,460 --> 00:37:15,420
but I’m still the one who evaluates your performance.

442
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,660
She only takes care of the documents.

443
00:37:19,330 --> 00:37:22,700
As for you, follow me to work on-site.

444
00:37:30,660 --> 00:37:32,660
Do I have to tell you everything?

445
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:35,260
Go drive.

446
00:37:41,930 --> 00:37:43,500
I don’t know how to drive.

447
00:37:48,730 --> 00:37:49,530
What?

448
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,460
You can’t blame me, Boss.

449
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:05,460
Not all of us were born knowing how to drive.

450
00:38:06,860 --> 00:38:09,820
Besides, it’s not like I don’t want to do it.

451
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:14,740
But…my family doesn’t encourage us women to do what men do.

452
00:38:15,780 --> 00:38:18,100
My older brothers have their own cars, so they had to learn how to drive.

453
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:24,700
I don’t have one, so my family told me to use public transportation instead.

454
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:28,020
Why dramatic all of a sudden?

455
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:32,860
I didn’t mean to be dramatic. I just wanted to explain it.

456
00:38:37,330 --> 00:38:41,100
While I’m driving, read these documents Miss Preem has prepared for us.

457
00:38:45,660 --> 00:38:49,140
We’ll reach there in half an hour.

458
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:51,300
Make sure you memorise everything.

459
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:55,660
All of them?

460
00:38:58,130 --> 00:38:59,730
It’s a lot. How could I memorise them in time?

461
00:39:02,700 --> 00:39:06,900
If you read every single line like that, it’d probably take you all day.

462
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:09,900
Just memorise the key points.

463
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:21,020
We’ll set up this side for salad bar, appetizers, and salad dressings.

464
00:39:21,020 --> 00:39:25,340
The main dishes will be here–be it pork, fish, or chicken. Put all of them here.

465
00:39:25,340 --> 00:39:32,180
And this side is a vegetarian zone. Make sure to put up a clear sign and provide different sets of dishes and utensils.

466
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:34,180
-Chef Ian?
- Next is the dessert zone.

467
00:39:35,180 --> 00:39:38,660
Is she the Michelin-star chef who went on an international cooking show?

468
00:39:38,660 --> 00:39:42,100
It takes years to get an appointment with her, Boss.

469
00:39:42,100 --> 00:39:45,220
It doesn’t matter how famous you are, you still have to wait.

470
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:49,700
Get yourself together. I know all that.

471
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:52,860
Do you have an appointment with them?

472
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:54,600
Oh, okay. That’s all then.

473
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:57,560
Hello.

474
00:39:58,660 --> 00:39:59,860
Hello, Chef.

475
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:02,960
Thank you for giving us your valuable time.

476
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,000
My pleasure.

477
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:10,660
This is Miss Chonlada, my secretary’s assistant.

478
00:40:10,860 --> 00:40:12,220
-Hello.
- Hello.

479
00:40:12,330 --> 00:40:14,700
I’ve already prepared the table for you, Miss Apo.

480
00:40:15,130 --> 00:40:18,060
Shall I take you there now to try my food?

481
00:40:18,060 --> 00:40:18,740
Yes.

482
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:20,330
Do we get to try your food too, Chef?

483
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:21,820
Yes.

484
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:23,180
You cooked it yourself?

485
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:24,460
Yes.

486
00:40:27,730 --> 00:40:28,530
I’m sorry.

487
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:29,380
Let’s go then, shall we?

488
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:30,060
Yes.

489
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:40,140
Please go ahead and try it.

490
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,000
Miss Chonlada.

491
00:40:59,660 --> 00:41:02,580
Oh, sorry, Boss.

492
00:41:03,180 --> 00:41:04,220
I’m sorry, Chef.

493
00:41:04,500 --> 00:41:07,900
Please don’t be. The customer’s reaction is the chef’s utmost happiness.

494
00:41:08,660 --> 00:41:11,100
Then, can I have one more bite?

495
00:41:11,300 --> 00:41:12,300
Of course.

496
00:41:21,060 --> 00:41:24,820
I’d rather wait until you and Boss finish talking then.

497
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,800
That’s all right. Please try it.

498
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:32,300
Thank you.

499
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:37,800
Actually, I think I know why you’re here, Miss Apo.

500
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:43,930
I hope you’ll finally agree and give us Watin Group the honour to welcome you this time.

501
00:41:44,930 --> 00:41:47,700
You just don’t know how to give up, do you?

502
00:41:47,700 --> 00:41:50,620
I had turned down your offer for so many times.

503
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:56,140
I’ll keep asking until you agree to work with us.

504
00:41:57,730 --> 00:42:00,220
I’m beginning to soften up a bit now.

505
00:42:01,330 --> 00:42:07,380
I still insist that no one else is suitable for this project other than you, Chef.

506
00:42:07,500 --> 00:42:10,060
Wow, I really appreciate that.

507
00:42:10,660 --> 00:42:14,020
How about you try it first?

508
00:42:14,330 --> 00:42:16,620
Okay. Thank you.

509
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,060
It’s really good.

510
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:27,400
What project are you planning to do with Chef Ian, Boss?

511
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,930
Haven’t you read the documents?

512
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:33,760
But there wasn’t any part that talks about Chef Ian.

513
00:42:34,600 --> 00:42:37,780
Only how to dispose of waste to help save the environment,

514
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:41,220
which is usually a fundamental knowledge for everyone, isn’t it?

515
00:42:41,500 --> 00:42:43,900
I don’t see any information that’s supposed to be confidential.

516
00:42:44,660 --> 00:42:49,060
Why? Do you want to have access to the hotel’s confidential information?

517
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:52,980
No, not at all. I was just explaining.

518
00:42:53,540 --> 00:42:57,980
You want me to help Miss Preem, don’t you? If I came to work knowing nothing,

519
00:42:57,980 --> 00:43:02,940
people might find it suspicious and think that I only got promoted because you want to keep me close to you.

520
00:43:03,860 --> 00:43:05,700
And they might start another rumour.

521
00:43:08,530 --> 00:43:10,820
Has anyone ever contacted you to go to Lopburi?

522
00:43:12,900 --> 00:43:15,330
No. Why?

523
00:43:15,660 --> 00:43:18,060
In case you can talk and make those monkeys fall asleep.

524
00:43:19,130 --> 00:43:21,540
Well, you hardly utter a word while I can’t stop talking.

525
00:43:21,540 --> 00:43:24,140
We’re a perfect match, aren’t we?

526
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:28,100
Anyway, what project are you planning to do with Chef Ian?

527
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,300
Hey, look out!

528
00:43:34,060 --> 00:43:35,140
Are you all right?

529
00:43:35,260 --> 00:43:37,260
I’m okay, Boss. Are you all right?

530
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:41,980
I’m so sorry. Are you all right, Miss Apo?

531
00:43:49,060 --> 00:43:51,600
There was a call so I got distracted and wasn’t looking.

532
00:43:53,060 --> 00:43:55,700
So, are you sure you and your friend are okay?

533
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:00,860
Yes.

534
00:44:01,820 --> 00:44:05,460
This is Chonlada, my secretary’s assistant.

535
00:44:06,530 --> 00:44:08,730
Huh? What about Miss Preem?

536
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:12,020
She’s at the office.

537
00:44:13,460 --> 00:44:16,360
You must be very busy. That's why you have to hire another secretary.

538
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:18,200
That’s understandable though, because right now the Watin Group’s hotels and resorts…

539
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:23,260
are indeed second to none.

540
00:44:23,260 --> 00:44:24,420
Please don’t say that.

541
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:29,960
If there’s nothing else, please excuse us then.

542
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:33,360
Did you come here to eat at Chef Ian’s restaurant?

543
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:38,100
I came for that too. But her assistant said she already had an appointment.

544
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:42,860
I guess that appointment was you then, Miss Apo.

545
00:44:44,100 --> 00:44:47,730
Actually, I’ve arranged an appointment with her beforehand many months ago.

546
00:44:48,660 --> 00:44:51,740
Mine is since last year but she still can’t give me her time slot.

547
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,820
It only took you months to get to meet with her.

548
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:57,500
Maybe I’ll have to ask for your advice.

549
00:44:58,060 --> 00:45:00,580
Why is it that you’re always one step ahead of the others?

550
00:45:01,100 --> 00:45:04,460
Well actually, you’ve been in this business before me, Mr. Pheempat.

551
00:45:05,300 --> 00:45:09,020
It’s rather me who has to ask for your advice.

552
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:17,000
Will you excuse us then? We have another matter to attend to.

553
00:45:17,660 --> 00:45:19,900
Sure. It’s a pleasure to meet you here.

554
00:45:20,540 --> 00:45:23,540
And a pleasure to meet you too, Miss Chonlada.

555
00:45:43,600 --> 00:45:45,060
Who removed your plug?

556
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:47,260
What plug?

557
00:45:48,330 --> 00:45:50,620
A plug to charge a battery for your mouth.

558
00:45:51,100 --> 00:45:53,360
You’ve been quiet since we left the restaurant.

559
00:45:53,800 --> 00:45:55,780
Or are you still in shock because you almost got hit by a car?

560
00:45:57,060 --> 00:45:58,500
Thank you for your concern, Boss.

561
00:46:00,600 --> 00:46:03,700
You didn’t even get hit, is your brain not functioning properly now?

562
00:46:05,500 --> 00:46:09,540
If you’re not worried about me, just deny it. What’s so hard about that?

563
00:46:11,930 --> 00:46:14,860
Hearing that, you seem pretty fine to me.

564
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:17,060
I feel bad for Miss Preem though.

565
00:46:17,380 --> 00:46:20,100
She’s just lost a chance to get rid of her annoying assistant.

566
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:28,140
I’m sorry, Boss. Are you all right?

567
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:31,380
Don’t you have eyes? Can’t you see I already stopped?

568
00:46:31,500 --> 00:46:34,060
Then why didn’t you tell me you’d stop?

569
00:46:34,930 --> 00:46:36,260
How could you blame it on me?

570
00:46:37,100 --> 00:46:41,300
Listen, I just want to tell you that you don’t have to follow me anymore.

571
00:46:41,700 --> 00:46:43,460
I’ll go inspect work by the beach.

572
00:46:44,060 --> 00:46:49,900
You should go tell Miss Preem to prepare documents for the campaign we’ll be promoting during the low season this year.

573
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:51,360
Yes, Boss.

574
00:47:02,560 --> 00:47:06,340
From next month onwards, we’ll offer mid-year promotions for the rainy season.

575
00:47:06,660 --> 00:47:09,580
The number of tourists, both Thai and foreign, will drop dramatically

576
00:47:09,580 --> 00:47:14,380
And when we have less bookings, it’ll certainly affect the costs, especially our payrolls.

577
00:47:14,380 --> 00:47:17,740
Same amount of staff but less amount of income.

578
00:47:20,220 --> 00:47:23,500
Is that why Boss came up with this campaign to attract more customers…

579
00:47:23,500 --> 00:47:26,820
and increase the booking rate?

580
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:31,020
Then, can we reduce the room rate?

581
00:47:31,020 --> 00:47:35,020
You can. But that’s what other hotels would do too.

582
00:47:35,020 --> 00:47:37,420
So, the booking rate won’t increase that much.

583
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:44,620
That’s why Boss wants Chef Ian to work with us on this campaign.

584
00:47:44,620 --> 00:47:48,940
Yes. She’s so talented and extremely hard to get an appointment with.

585
00:47:49,260 --> 00:47:55,380
So, if we can get her to cook for our hotel, that’d help increase our booking rate, right?

586
00:48:01,400 --> 00:48:05,180
At first, when Boss told me that you’d be my assistant;

587
00:48:06,660 --> 00:48:09,620
to be honest, I had so many doubts in my mind.

588
00:48:10,380 --> 00:48:14,180
Boss doesn’t easily trust anyone to work closely with her.

589
00:48:14,540 --> 00:48:18,900
I got this job because my aunt used to be the Big Boss’s secretary.

590
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:20,740
He certified me for the job.

591
00:48:20,740 --> 00:48:25,140
why did Boss agree to let you work with her so easily?

592
00:48:25,900 --> 00:48:28,140
I think I understand now.

593
00:48:31,500 --> 00:48:32,980
You understand what?

594
00:48:36,300 --> 00:48:39,800
She must have known more about you than I do.

595
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:48,180
Know what about me?

596
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:56,340
Boss probably knows what someone who’s confident like you could do to help.

597
00:48:56,900 --> 00:49:01,340
At least, you’re not afraid to be honest with her…

598
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:03,340
rather than lying just to please her.

599
00:49:03,740 --> 00:49:08,100
You’re also a fast learner as if you had an experience working at a hotel before.

600
00:49:12,060 --> 00:49:14,340
I did an internship while studying.

601
00:49:14,530 --> 00:49:17,180
That’s why I learnt about the hotel system pretty fast.

602
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:20,380
But there’s still a lot I have to learn, and you must teach me that.

603
00:49:24,160 --> 00:49:27,300
Well then, I’ll go destroy these documents first.

604
00:49:27,300 --> 00:49:28,900
I’ll be right back to help.

605
00:50:26,300 --> 00:50:27,380
Boo!

606
00:50:29,780 --> 00:50:31,860
A scaredy cat as usual.

607
00:50:31,900 --> 00:50:33,500
You scared me to death, Fah!

608
00:50:33,930 --> 00:50:34,940
When did you get here?

609
00:50:34,960 --> 00:50:36,700
Been waiting for you since afternoon.

610
00:50:38,100 --> 00:50:39,860
I took so many naps.

611
00:50:40,700 --> 00:50:42,180
- You scared me.
-  I miss you. Give me a hug.

612
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:44,580
Miss you so much.

613
00:50:44,860 --> 00:50:46,060
Hold on. Stop it. Stop.

614
00:50:46,860 --> 00:50:48,580
- Let me go.
- Miss you so much.

615
00:50:48,580 --> 00:50:50,060
- It’s been a long time.
- Don’t lie.

616
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:52,940
- We talked on the phone a few days ago.
- Please give me a hug. Pleaseeee.

617
00:50:52,940 --> 00:50:55,700
Fah! Behave.

618
00:50:56,660 --> 00:50:59,000
What do you mean you miss me? We just talked a few days ago.

619
00:50:59,330 --> 00:51:01,300
But it’s not like seeing you in person.

620
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,700
You also don’t have time for me at all.

621
00:51:04,330 --> 00:51:06,060
Mum’s complaining now.

622
00:51:07,060 --> 00:51:09,500
I’ll find some time to Facetime her then.

623
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:11,820
Why did you come to Thailand?

624
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:13,060
To get a scoop?

625
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:15,020
Not really.

626
00:51:15,500 --> 00:51:17,340
I still don’t find any interesting topics.

627
00:51:17,340 --> 00:51:19,300
So, I’ll come live with you in the meantime.

628
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:22,260
If there happens to be anything interesting, I’ll think about it then.

629
00:51:22,530 --> 00:51:26,020
But I’m not sure if you’ll have time for me though.

630
00:51:27,730 --> 00:51:29,500
I heard you already have a girlfriend.

631
00:51:33,530 --> 00:51:34,820
Did Dad tell you?

632
00:51:35,730 --> 00:51:37,860
I want to see your girlfriend.

633
00:51:38,330 --> 00:51:40,460
Can I go see my future sister-in-law tomorrow?

634
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:42,900
Can I see her? Pleaseee.

635
00:51:43,500 --> 00:51:45,740
- Can I?
- Chonlada and I are not together.

636
00:51:45,800 --> 00:51:50,420
Wait, Miss Chonlada?

637
00:51:57,330 --> 00:52:00,540
Chonlada means waves.

638
00:52:01,400 --> 00:52:03,300
Apo means water.

639
00:52:03,960 --> 00:52:06,540
What else could this be if not soulmates?

640
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:09,900
That woman has already given me enough headache.

641
00:52:10,130 --> 00:52:11,740
No need to create more problems for me.

642
00:52:12,260 --> 00:52:13,500
Not to mention Lom.

643
00:52:13,960 --> 00:52:16,980
And that rumour. And Dad too.

644
00:52:23,730 --> 00:52:24,530
Why are you smiling?

645
00:52:25,700 --> 00:52:28,800
Miss Chonlada isn’t the first woman who came into your life.

646
00:52:29,800 --> 00:52:30,600
So?

647
00:52:31,130 --> 00:52:33,460
But you’ve never talked about any woman like this before.

648
00:52:33,820 --> 00:52:34,700
Fah.

649
00:52:36,060 --> 00:52:44,300
I guess she might be that someone who can finally make your icy heart waver.

650
00:52:45,730 --> 00:52:47,000
I’m not talking to you then.

651
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:51,530
That’s fine. I can go talk to your dad.

652
00:53:03,530 --> 00:53:04,700
Uncle! Uncle!

653
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:10,300
How was it? Did she mention anything about Lada?

654
00:53:10,330 --> 00:53:13,060
She kept denying but she just couldn’t stop talking about her.

655
00:53:13,460 --> 00:53:15,060
So, do you think she likes her?

656
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:17,660
I’d say 80% positive, Uncle.

657
00:53:17,730 --> 00:53:19,340
Okay.

658
00:53:21,200 --> 00:53:26,860
Uncle, do you know what Miss Chonlada’s, my future sister-in-law’s family name is?

659
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:29,100
Why?

660
00:53:30,300 --> 00:53:32,540
I’m just being nosy as usual.

661
00:53:32,540 --> 00:53:35,740
If I ask Nam, she definitely wouldn’t tell me.

662
00:53:35,740 --> 00:53:41,020
I want to use my connection as a journalist to find out about Miss Chonlada more.

663
00:53:52,860 --> 00:53:54,780
Did Apo just let you out?

664
00:53:56,360 --> 00:53:57,340
Pat?

665
00:53:57,930 --> 00:54:00,860
How did you get here?

666
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:04,580
Why didn’t you tell me…

667
00:54:04,940 --> 00:54:07,540
that you’re now her secretary’s assistant?

668
00:54:08,700 --> 00:54:11,900
I just got promoted today.

669
00:54:12,160 --> 00:54:16,060
Besides, I never thought I’d get to see you and Miss Apo together.

670
00:54:18,130 --> 00:54:21,100
I’m sorry. I only stopped by to see Chef Ian.

671
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:26,300
But I’m glad that you can get close to Apo this fast.

672
00:54:26,660 --> 00:54:29,140
This way, you can help dig out more information for me.

673
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:35,160
So, did Chef Ian finally agree to work with the Watin Group?

674
00:54:38,160 --> 00:54:40,400
And what project that your boss is planning to do with her?

675
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:57,260
[Lada]: I miss you.

676
00:54:57,300 --> 00:54:58,740
But I don’t miss you.

677
00:55:04,530 --> 00:55:05,760
[Lada]: I want to talk to you.

678
00:55:06,130 --> 00:55:07,530
But I don’t want to talk to you.

679
00:55:10,260 --> 00:55:12,330
[Lada]: I have something to tell you about Pat.

680
00:55:12,800 --> 00:55:13,800
I don’t want to hear it!

681
00:55:20,730 --> 00:55:23,100
[Lada]: Not answering means you’re still mad at me.

682
00:55:23,100 --> 00:55:26,500
[Lada]: I’ll go tell it to someone else then. I won’t bother you anymore.

683
00:55:26,500 --> 00:55:27,900
Whatever.

684
00:55:30,700 --> 00:55:31,500
So?

685
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:33,620
So what?

686
00:55:33,700 --> 00:55:36,100
You’re the one who texted me first.

687
00:55:36,530 --> 00:55:38,140
You forgave me, right?

688
00:55:40,700 --> 00:55:43,380
No, but it’s annoying.

689
00:55:43,380 --> 00:55:47,340
If I hadn’t call you, I guess you would’ve texted me all night.

690
00:55:47,340 --> 00:55:48,620
So, how is it?

691
00:55:49,220 --> 00:55:53,020
Disguising yourself as an employee at your rival’s hotel.

692
00:55:53,020 --> 00:55:55,460
Have you got any insider news for your brothe

693
00:55:57,900 --> 00:55:58,940
Yes.

694
00:55:59,580 --> 00:56:02,780
Miss Apo is trying to get Chef Ian to work with her on a new project.

695
00:56:02,780 --> 00:56:06,420
But I didn’t tell my brother that.

696
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:09,460
Huh? Why not?

697
00:56:12,260 --> 00:56:14,530
[Pheempat]: What project that your boss is planning to do with Chef Ian?

698
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:17,980
I really have no idea.

699
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:23,860
But weren’t you also there at the restaurant with her?

700
00:56:24,500 --> 00:56:26,540
How come you didn’t get any information?

701
00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:33,140
Like I said, this is my first day as her assistant.

702
00:56:33,140 --> 00:56:35,660
She still doesn't trust me that much.

703
00:56:36,560 --> 00:56:38,360
I’m afraid I don’t have anything for you.

704
00:56:41,700 --> 00:56:42,660
Lada…

705
00:56:43,330 --> 00:56:45,530
You do know that you’re my only hope, don’t you?

706
00:56:46,760 --> 00:56:50,380
If my hotel becomes a success, it’s not just me that you could save.

707
00:56:51,100 --> 00:56:53,200
But you could also save the Wachara Group as a whole.

708
00:56:54,100 --> 00:56:55,800
And Dad will look at you with new eyes.

709
00:56:57,730 --> 00:56:59,460
But if my hotel goes down,

710
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:03,380
apart from me losing all the credits in Dad’s eyes;

711
00:57:03,900 --> 00:57:07,020
you’ll end up being just a daughter who’s merely nothing,

712
00:57:07,740 --> 00:57:10,540
but an object to trade-off for business negotiations.

713
00:57:13,000 --> 00:57:14,740
Do you understand what I mean?

714
00:57:34,130 --> 00:57:37,200
I’ve never forgotten why I chose to work at the Watin Group.

715
00:57:38,600 --> 00:57:41,460
Then, why didn’t you tell your brother about Chef Ian?

716
00:57:42,100 --> 00:57:45,620
Because Miss Apo didn’t play dirty to get Chef Ian to work with her.

717
00:57:46,180 --> 00:57:49,900
But if one day the Watin Group ever tries to play dirty with the Wachara Group,

718
00:57:49,900 --> 00:57:52,060
I’ll tell my brother everything.

719
00:57:52,660 --> 00:57:54,980
I totally agree and I support you fully.

720
00:57:55,260 --> 00:57:59,160
We should at least play it fair and square.

721
00:57:59,930 --> 00:58:07,940
But honestly, maybe it’s better if you back out before Miss Apo would find out who you really are.

722
00:58:09,330 --> 00:58:10,420
Back out?

723
00:58:11,200 --> 00:58:15,940
Do you know how hard it is to get attention from someone who doesn’t care about the world like her,

724
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:17,620
and make her finally remember my name

725
00:58:17,860 --> 00:58:19,220
I can’t back out right now.

726
00:58:19,700 --> 00:58:23,700
I can only go forward, and make her trust me.

727
00:58:24,130 --> 00:58:27,000
I need to dig out more information from the Watin Group.

728
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:31,740
You’d better be careful then.

729
00:58:32,060 --> 00:58:35,380
You’ve put yourself inside the lion’s den. It’s risky.

730
00:58:35,900 --> 00:58:38,780
But I’m afraid something is riskier.

731
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:44,020
Riskier? What do you mean?

732
00:58:45,460 --> 00:58:52,060
Listen to me, Lada. You’re playing with people’s feelings.

733
00:58:52,060 --> 00:58:56,540
You’re in this game too. Just make sure you won’t fall into your own trap.

734
00:58:57,500 --> 00:59:00,860
Wait, you think I’d fall for her?

735
00:59:01,160 --> 00:59:02,780
Dream on.

736
00:59:03,460 --> 00:59:04,820
You can place your bet.

737
00:59:04,820 --> 00:59:06,260
I’ll definitely win.

738
00:59:07,730 --> 00:59:10,580
Nate, I have another call. I’ll call you back.

739
00:59:10,860 --> 00:59:14,140
Huh? What the…

740
00:59:14,960 --> 00:59:16,160
Hello, who’s speaking?

741
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:19,200
It’s me.

742
00:59:25,100 --> 00:59:29,220
Boss? How did you get my number?

743
00:59:31,700 --> 00:59:33,960
The HR department has all of the staff’s phone numbers.

744
00:59:34,600 --> 00:59:36,560
You’re my secretary’s assistant.

745
00:59:36,900 --> 00:59:38,500
Do you think it’s that hard to get your number?

746
00:59:40,960 --> 00:59:44,940
I’m sorry. I totally forgot my boss has an extremely high IQ.

747
00:59:45,580 --> 00:59:48,660
Calling me at this hour, what can I do for you?

748
00:59:52,530 --> 00:59:53,700
Have you taken your pills?

749
00:59:55,940 --> 00:59:56,780
Yes?

750
00:59:59,100 --> 01:00:03,760
Miss Preem told me you walked back home in the rain.

751
01:00:06,700 --> 01:00:07,700
Take some medicine too.

752
01:00:08,900 --> 01:00:10,900
And don’t think it’s because I’m concerned.

753
01:00:11,660 --> 01:00:13,260
I’m not worried about you.

754
01:00:14,100 --> 01:00:15,580
I’m more worried about myself.

755
01:00:16,060 --> 01:00:17,820
I don’t want to work with a sick person.

756
